abstract: Author Julian Barnes is awarded Man Booker Prize for his novel The Sense of An Ending.
snippet: The novelist Julian Barnes won the Man Booker Prize on Tuesday night for “The Sense of an Ending,” a slim and meditative story of mortality, frustration and regret.
lead_paragraph: The novelist Julian Barnes won the Man Booker Prize on Tuesday night for “The Sense of an Ending,” a slim and meditative story of mortality, frustration and regret.
